docs.lead_paragraph: DEATH OF MISS MARY MATHER.--Yesterday the telegraph communicated to her relatives in this City the painful intelligence of the sudden deaths of Miss MARY MATHER, who left home for New-York, in her usual state of health, on Friday.

docs.lead_paragraph: THE DOCTOR AND THE SEXTON.-A good story is told of a doctor in Beverly, who was somewhat of a wag. He met one day in the street, the sexton with whom he was acquainted. As the usual salutations were passed, the doctor happened to cough.

byline.original: SPECIAL CORRESPONDENCE OF THE NEW-YORK DAILY TIMES

docs.lead_paragraph: We have received Jamaica papers to Feb. 7. The Port Maria Westermost River overflowed its banks on Wednesday, the 3d, a quarter of a mile above the town, and in about ten minutes the water rushed through the houses and stores to some extent. In the Post Office, the water rose fully twenty inches, and in the streets it was at least three or four feet in depth.

headline.main: LATEST INTELLIGENCE; By Telegraph to the New-York Daily Times. XXXIId CONGRESS... Second Session. SENATE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES. NEW-YORK STATE LEGISLATURE. ASSEMBLY,

docs.lead_paragraph: The Senate was called to order at 20 minutes past 11 o'clock. Mr. GWIN moved to take up the Pacific Railroad bill, which was agreed to. Mr. HAMLIN gave notice that on Monday he would move to take up the bill (Miss DIX's) for the benefit of the indigent insane.
